1276 The writer makes “cherubim”—or “cherubin”—singular. I have therefore retained his mistake. What
the “hot point”—“calidus apex”—is, is not clear. It may be an allusion to the “flaming sword” (see Gen. iii. 24);
or it may mean the top of the flame.

